# chain.word — what a CHAIN is, an order of acts or of facts, sealed.
# The host calls a chain a reel (seed/past/reel/ — reelHead.js, reelHeads.js, appendLock.js).
# The host counter, hash, and lock stay. Descends from word.word and base.word. Every word in it
# is grounded (chain, act, fact, order, head, hash). A Name's chain is an act chain. A being's, a
# space's, a matter's chain is a fact chain. Those kinds, and the single writer, are told where
# their nouns are, above this.

A chain is an order of acts or of facts.
A chain has a head, its last, and a hash over all before it.
The hash seals the chain, so its past cannot be forged or reordered.
